The following terms are use in the source code repeatedly in a consistent
manner:

`date` — a date in form "YYYYMMDD"

`reprocess` — process a date again, but first clear the results from previous
processing

`run` — a run of the pipeline on a single day

`validation` — the process of determining if a file is valid, i.e., it has the
correct format, metadata, etc.

`verification` — the process of determining if the processing has been
completed correctly for a day
